# 🧠 Now we can think why we need tuple if we have list , because list is mutable and has more methods than tuple , so we will understand why we need tuple and why we use it
# so we will some key difference between list and tuple
# 1. tuple are immutable and list are mutable
# 2. tuple uses parentheses and list uses square brackets
# 3. tuple is faster than list 
# 4. tuple uses less memory than list

# so finally, use tuple when your data is constant, but if you want to make changes in your data then use list
# now we will check practically the memory size difference between tuple and list, for that first we will import sys 

import sys
print("tuple size :- " ,sys.getsizeof((1 , 2 , 3)))
print("list size :- " ,sys.getsizeof([1 , 2 , 3]))
# we can see here that we are using same data in both tuple and list , but see the memory size difference between tuple and list
print("\n")


